<!-- Game Controls Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>&nbsp;<u><i><font color="#FFFF00">MENUS CONTROLS:</font></i></u><br>
                  &nbsp; Move highlight to next item or adjacent column:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;D-Pad</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Choose highlighted item; in text and number of grids, choose highlighted letter or symbol:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;X Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; In menus with a statistical set button, tap repeatedly to cycle through the four statistical sets; press and hold for 2 seconds, then release to reveal the statistical display screen:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Circle Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Cancel:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Square Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Move highlight to next list:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Select Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Choose default menu item:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Start Button</font><br>
			<br>&nbsp;<u><i><font color="#FFFF00">BATTING & BASERUNNING CONTROLS:</font></i></u><br>
                  &nbsp; Move highlight to desired batting option; target swing location in strike zone. also by pressing the directional buttons to the corresponding base, you can advance the runner to the next base. by pressing the previous base and the X button, you can retreat to the previous base. leading off and stealing can be accomplished by holding down the directional button of the next base and then stealing by pressing the Circle button:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;D-Pad</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Choose highlighted batting option; swing bat; combine with directional button to return runner to previous base:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;X Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Press and hold to display batter/pitcher's card while in batting options menu. press and hold again to view the backside with statistics:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Circle Button</font><br>
			<br>&nbsp;<u><i><font color="#FFFF00">PITCHING & FIELDING CONTROLS:</font></i></u><br>
                  &nbsp; Move highlight to desired pitching option; aim pitch; move highlighted fielder:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;D-Pad</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Choose highlighted pitching option; throw pitch; combine with a directional buttion to throw to base; switch control to fielder closest to ball:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;X Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Make fileder dive or jump for the ball; combine with a directional button to attempt a pickoff; display batter/pitcher's card while in pitching options menu:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Circle Button</font><br>
			<br>&nbsp;<u><i><font color="#FFFF00">OTHER ACTIONS CONTROLS:</font></i></u><br>
                  &nbsp; Display windsock and scoreboard during gameplay:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Square Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Call time out and view the scoreboard/lineup screen:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Select Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Pause or resume gameplay:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Start Button</font><br><br>
        &nbsp;</td>
	 </tr>
	</table>
       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>

      
